A syringe and a dose of the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine. AFP/Sameer Al-Doumy JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Health confirmed 14,410 new cases of COVID-19 since the last report. The department also reported a further 513 deaths, taking South Africa's COVID-19 death toll to over 30,500. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Health workers share fears and experiences Meanwhile, President Cyril Ramaphosa has called an urgent meeting of the National Coronavirus Command Council. The announcement of an adjusted Level 3 Lockdown, has been criticised by several sectors. Many are also slamming the government's vaccine rollout plan. On Sunday, the Health Minister announced plans to vaccinate 40-million people by the end of the year. #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 05 January .
